#
# Temporary KiriView Flatpak packaging patch.
#
# libheif 1.20.2 has an FFmpeg decoder plugin, but upstream only advertises it
# for HEVC and reconstructs an HEVC-specific NAL stream. KiriView needs AVC HEIF
# still-image decoding.
#
# As of May 2026, that sample stores the visible color image as AVC 4:2:0. Its
# user-visible alpha channel is stored as a separate HEIF alpha auxiliary image,
# referenced through auxl and described by auxC, encoded as a monochrome AVC
# 4:0:0 item. The libheif OpenH264 path did not decode that alpha auxiliary item,
# so the full image failed even though the color item could be decoded separately.
#
# This patch extends the FFmpeg plugin to accept AVC as well as HEVC and feeds
# FFmpeg an Annex-B stream built from all length-prefixed NAL units. FFmpeg's
# H.264 decoder handles both the color item and the alpha auxiliary item in the
# sample. Remove this patch when upstream libheif can decode AVC HEIF still
# images, including alpha auxiliary images, without this downstream change.

